2004: A violent earthquake on the west coast of Indonesia's Aceh province in northern Sumatra triggered a tsunami on 26 December that hit 14 countries and killed 226,000 people along the Indian Ocean coast, including over half of them in Aceh.
2005: A series of severe earthquakes hit the west coast of Sumatra in late March and only in April.
Hundreds died on the island of Nias off the coast of Sumatra.
2006: An earthquake measuring 6.8 struck south of Java, Indonesia's most densely populated island, triggering a tsunami that hit the southern coast and killed nearly 700 people.
2009: An earthquake of 7.6 struck near the city of Padang, the capital of western Sumatra province.
