2010: An earthquake measuring 7.5 struck one of the Mentawai Islands off Sumatra and triggered a tsunami of up to 10 meters that destroyed dozens of villages and killed about 300 people.
2016: A surface earthquake hit the Aceh regency and spread destruction and panic as the population was reminded of the deadly 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
